00:13:52,422 --> 00:13:54,283
Can I get this concept to...

254
00:13:54,283 --> 00:13:57,784
Can I think of where it could be applied somewhere like that?

255
00:13:57,784 --> 00:14:00,486
And if I can't, then I should go back and rework the concept.

256
00:14:00,486 --> 00:14:02,186
Same thing with technology.

257
00:14:02,186 --> 00:14:03,727
If I can't...

258
00:14:03,727 --> 00:14:06,188
If I'm thinking about something in terms of Unreal

259
00:14:06,188 --> 00:14:08,449
and I can't think of it in terms of Unity,

260
00:14:08,449 --> 00:14:10,750
then it's only useful to the Unreal audience

261
00:14:10,750 --> 00:14:12,351
and therefore invalid.

262
00:14:12,351 --> 00:14:16,253
Because you want to make things as useful to everybody

263
00:14:16,253 --> 00:14:17,853
who's a level designer as possible.

264
00:14:19,606 --> 00:14:24,228
So that's talking without identifying your game,

265
00:14:24,228 --> 00:14:27,089
without speaking about your specific game.

266
00:14:27,089 --> 00:14:28,570
Another thing you can do is sketch ideas

267
00:14:28,570 --> 00:14:30,510
without content that identifies your game.

268
00:14:30,510 --> 00:14:33,732
Again, I can take a concept like creating

269
00:14:33,732 --> 00:14:35,592
the feeling of curiosity in players

270
00:14:35,592 --> 00:14:39,114
with rhythmic elements and shaded lighting conditions,

271
00:14:39,114 --> 00:14:41,675
which this is a diagram of,

272
00:14:41,675 --> 00:14:43,756
and I don't have to draw a specific game.

273
00:14:43,756 --> 00:14:45,996
I can just draw pillars and some light

274
00:14:45,996 --> 00:14:47,857
and a stick figure that's going, ooh.

275
00:14:49,027 --> 00:14:53,550
